      "content": "hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive controller and i've got a weird issue. the system's RAM usage just keeps climbing slowly over like 4 or 5 hours until it hits the limit and crashes. i've checked some of the main loops but i can't find where the allocation isn't being freed. can you give me a systematic way to track down where these leaks are happening?",
